cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with improving the throughput performance of wireless networks through a distributed scheduling mechanism. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves optimizing access probabilities and thresholds to maximize throughput performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes an adaptive algorithm based on control theory to adjust the access probability and threshold of each station. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper may involve measuring channel conditions for multimedia transmission. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possibility as the paper aims to optimize throughput performance in terms of proportional fairness.
